			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Sitting</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"Sit" redirects here. For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Sit_(disambiguation)" class="mw-redirect mw-disambig" title="Sit (disambiguation)">Sit (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Werner_Stoetzer_Sitzender_Junge.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Werner_Stoetzer_Sitzender_Junge.jpg/220px-Werner_Stoetzer_Sitzender_Junge.jpg" width="220" height="360" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Werner_Stoetzer_Sitzender_Junge.jpg/330px-Werner_Stoetzer_Sitzender_Junge.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/23/Werner_Stoetzer_Sitzender_Junge.jpg 2x" data-file-width="378" data-file-height="618" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Werner_Stoetzer_Sitzender_Junge.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>
<i>Sitzender Junge</i> ("Sitting boy") by <a href="/wiki/Werner_St%C3%B6tzer" title="Werner Stötzer">Werner Stötzer</a>, 1956</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Sitting</b> is a <a href="/wiki/List_of_human_positions" title="List of human positions">basic human resting position</a>. The body weight is supported primarily by the <a href="/wiki/Buttocks" title="Buttocks">buttocks</a> in contact with the ground or a horizontal object such as a <a href="/wiki/Chair_seat" class="mw-redirect" title="Chair seat">chair seat</a>. The <a href="/wiki/Torso" title="Torso">torso</a> is more or less upright. Sitting for much of the day may pose significant health risks, and people who sit regularly for prolonged periods have higher mortality rates than those who do not.<sup id="cite_ref-Biswas_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Biswas-1">[1]</a></sup></p>
<p>The form of <a href="/wiki/Kneeling" title="Kneeling">kneeling</a> where the thighs are near horizontal and the buttocks sit back on the heels, for example as in <a href="/wiki/Seiza" title="Seiza">Seiza</a> and <a href="/wiki/Vajrasana_(yoga)" title="Vajrasana (yoga)">Vajrasana (yoga)</a>, is also often interpreted as sitting.</p>
<p></p>
